This is almost always caused by a stale cache or incompatible versions.

You are using the Eclipse 3.2, so you must be using VE 1.2, so if you are not using VE 1.2, then upgrade to VE 1.2M1.

If you are at VE 1.2, then this is usually a stale cache. So try this in that case:

1) Open a VE and close it and ALL VE. There should be none open. Ignore errors.
2) Now do a Project->Clean...->Clean All
3) Wait for the build to complete
4) Try the VE again and see if you still get the problem. Reply back here with result please.
